I hope you are having a incredible progress on your new year project, here is some idea for new years in China where I growed up.

Firstly, new years in China are insane, we always feels like a new self. Your facts, kind of resets at a new year, that's only one of those reasons. One of my most intrested in is people litterally turns into a lion, dance on a TV show that happens once in a year, which is the new years that starts at 0am sharp.

By talking about the TV show, that is basicaly how we celebrates usally, but there is like an invisible scedule. like you wake up in new years eve, starts to prepare for the craziness, and then when the clock hits 0:00, the craziness begins.

People are talking non-stop, all lights are lighted, people that are stressed will stop their work and start waching the TV show, no one sleeps except for kids for sure. They will gossip, and there will always a student with a magna cum laude and their parents are cool, I absolutely loved this atmosphere.

One day, we went to the neighbours in the new years at 2am in the morning, they are stil awake, celebrating with their friends, families etc..

In China, this is not just a tradition, it is a unite where everyone are full with joy, it is probably one of the most expected days in China at least in my opinion.

